article.headline: Balanced scoring attack leads Alcorn State past UAPB 79-60

images.name: T. Wilson made Three Point Jumper.
images.caption: 1H (15:33) ALCN Tamarcio Wilson made Three Point Jumper.

article.linkText: Balanced scoring attack leads Alcorn State past UAPB 79-60
article.story: LORMAN, Miss. -- Tamarcio Wilson scored 12 points, while Devonte Hampton, Rahamanh Katumbusi II and Marquis Vance added 10 points apiece to help Alcorn State beat Arkansas-Pine Bluff 79-60 Monday night. It was a career high for the freshman Katumbusi, who averages 1.9 points. Twelve different Alcorn State players scored as the Braves shot a season-high 54.5 percent (24 of 44) from the field and hit 11 of 19 (57.9 percent) from 3-point range. Alcorn State (12-12, 10-3 Southwestern Athletic Conference) scored the first eight points and a layup by Reginald Johnson made it 15-2 midway through the first half. The Braves led 39-21 at the break. Vance hit two 3s during an 11-1 run that gave Alcorn State a 64-33 lead, its biggest of the game, with 8:22 left. Charles Jackson led UAPB (6-21, 4-9) with 18 points on 7-of-13 shooting, including all four of the Golden Lions' made 3-pointers. They finished 4 of 25 (16 percent) from behind the arc.
